items.title: Austrolestes analis
items.content_text: ID confirmation by RNR who added "Diagnostic feature is the "hook" to the rear of the thorax under the antehumeral stripe" which I have highlighted in the 3rd pic/collage.

items.title: Austrolestes leda
items.content_text: Male 'guarding' female as she lays eggs on Triglochin procera s.l.. New species record for Riddells Creek (no. 21). 11th species recorded at Wybejong.

items.title: Ischnura aurora
items.content_text: Tiny damselfly. New species record for Riddells Creek.

items.title: Cordulephya pygmaea
items.content_text: Autumn flying dragonfly. Rests with wings held shut.

items.title: Austrolestes leda

items.title: Austrolestes annulosus
items.content_text: New species record for Riddells Creek. Now at 25% of all Vic dragonflies.

items.title: Hemicordulia tau
items.content_text: Wouldn't land so had to try and get pics while in flight.

items.title: Hemicordulia australiae
items.content_text: Mating pair. New species record for Riddells Creek.

items.title: Ischnura heterosticta heterosticta
items.content_text: Two spots on back of the head is a distinguishing feature for this species.

items.title: Diplacodes bipunctata
items.content_text: Flying in a dried up, rocky creek bed along with male D. haematodes and male O. caledonicum among other species.

items.title: Cordulephya pygmaea
items.content_text: Tiny dragonfly (a true dragonfly with the wings held together - like a damselfly). A new species record for Riddells Creek.

items.title: Orthetrum caledonicum
items.content_text: I saw this dragonfly tucking into what looks like a fly or bee (looks a bit like a Cuckoo Bee). No females observed.

items.title: Diplacodes haematodes
items.content_text: New species record for Riddells Creek. 2nd & 3rd pic shows yellowish colouring on proximal half of wing - an ID feature for this species. No females seen.

items.title: Austroaeschna multipunctata
items.content_text: Ovipositing in very shallow water, right on the water's edge where the water wasn't really flowing.

items.title: Synthemis eustalacta
items.content_text: Mating pair. Flying around Triglochin striata (Streaked Arrowgrass) on the edge of swamp.

items.title: Austroaeschna multipunctata
items.content_text: Landed on the back lawn with numerous people sitting around. Lots of dragonflies around today.

items.title: Xanthagrion erythroneurum
items.content_text: On a winter-wet, summer-dry grassland area, road on one side, rail on the other side, no permanent water in the vicinity. New species record for Riddells Creek.

items.title: Austrogomphus guerini
items.content_text: Spotted resting on Ozothamnus obcordatus by Steve Williams during a joint RCLandcare-Entomological Society night.

items.title: Hemianax papuensis

items.title: Austroargiolestes icteromelas
items.content_text: Very friendly. Initially spotted on concrete by my daughter Ellena.

items.title: Austroargiolestes icteromelas
items.content_text: Sitting on the grass in the garden and it landed on Gill's hand. I think it is female.

items.title: Austrolestes analis
items.content_text: Probably female (females seem to be very variable in colouring).

items.title: Austroargiolestes icteromelas
items.content_text: Unusual for a damselfly that it holds its wings spread out. Large for a damselfly (but considerably smaller than your average dragonfly).

items.title: Ischnura heterosticta heterosticta
items.content_text: 2 x blue post-occipital blue spots are a key ID feature. 3rd photo (full size) shows what it is holding with two front legs, and eating, has legs. This observation & 4669 are of the same individual & good for ID.

items.title: Telephlebiidae spp.
items.content_text: Looking for bugs in Sandy Creek. We found more bugs on the side of the creek than the centre.
